Document: AtlasTexture
Path: godot/classes/class_atlastexture.rst
Summary: A Texture2D resource that displays a portion of an atlas texture, with adjustable region and margin settings.

AtlasTexture is a Texture2D resource that draws only part of its atlas texture, as defined by the region property. An additional margin can be set for small adjustments. Multiple AtlasTexture resources can be cropped from the same atlas texture, allowing efficient packing of smaller textures into a single large texture to optimize video memory usage and reduce render calls.

Note: AtlasTexture cannot be used in an AnimatedTexture and will not tile properly in nodes like TextureRect or Sprite2D. To achieve tiling, modify the region property instead. The atlas property references the source texture, while the region defines the visible portion. The margin property provides fine-grained control for adjustments. Inherits: Texture2D.
