Document: AtlasTexture
Path: godot/classes/class_atlastexture.rst
Summary: Properties and member variables of the AtlasTexture class, including atlas texture, filter settings, margins, and region definitions.

AtlasTexture properties:
- atlas (Texture2D): The texture containing the atlas. Can be any Texture2D subclass including another AtlasTexture. Set via set_atlas(Texture2D), retrieved via get_atlas() → Texture2D.
- filter_clip (bool): If true, area outside the region is clipped to avoid texture pixel bleeding. Default: false. Set via set_filter_clip(bool), checked via has_filter_clip() → bool.
- margin (Rect2): Margin around the region for adjustments. If Rect2.size is set, texture is resized to fit within margin. Default: Rect2(0,0,0,0). Set via set_margin(Rect2), retrieved via get_margin() → Rect2.
- region (Rect2): Defines the area to draw from the atlas. If region size dimensions are 0, uses atlas size for that axis. Default: Rect2(0,0,0,0). Set via set_region(Rect2), retrieved via get_region() → Rect2. Note: Image size is always integer, so region size is rounded down.